defaultOverviewdefault default&#xa0;
defaultWithin the Creative Skillset’s governance structure, the BBC is represented on our Board, our National Boards in Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland
default and many of our relevant sector skills councils (see also above)
default&#xa0;
defaultAnne Morrison (Director of BBC Academy) chairs our 
defaultDigital Content and TV Strategy Group
default, chairs our advisory group for Hiive, a Creative Skillset new online platform for p
defaultrofessional devel
defaultopment, and
default sits in the Creative Industries Council Skills Group; the new Director General of the BBC, Lord Tony Hall, is also one of our Patrons.
default&#xa0;
defaultOther BBC staff are involved in other panels and task-and-finish groups which are for qualification and curr
defaulticulum development (i.e. development of Apprenticeship Frameworks, development of Vocational Qualifications and Standards), geographical cluster groups (i.e. Bristol Anchor, MediaCityUK) and Training Provision related groups (i.e. the accreditation of HE c
defaultourses, apprenticeship providers and short courses groups). The BBC also actively contributes to our
default research portfolio and
default participates in our intelligence gathering about the skills needs of the industry. 
default&#xa0;
defaultWithin our partnership work, the BBC contribute
defaults financially to the core budget of Creative Skillset, a
defaultnd 
defaultto the TV Freelance Training Fund. It also co-invests directly through providing Apprenticeships, work experience, trainee positions and internships, and short training events for Freelancers, like
default 
defaultFastTrain
default.
default The BBC also contributes directly to training institutions like the National Film and Television School. 
